cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for recognizing crowd behavior in videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves developing methods for recognizing visual crowd behavioral attributes without any training samples, which falls under the category of zero-shot learning. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. The paper also involves exploring multiattribute cooccurrence as contextual knowledge for optimizing individual crowd attribute recognition, which falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category. The paper also involves analyzing and modeling crowd behavior in videos, which falls under the category of multimedia. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a likely category. Finally, the paper also involves surveillance videos, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another likely category.
